---
By: Ralph W. Emerson
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 375
    Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Prayer
---
Prayer as a means to effect a privateend is theft and meanness. It
supposesdualism in nature and consciousness. As soon as the man is one with
God he will not beg. He will then see prayer inall action.
